Broadcast
Objective

Allow admins (users marked admin in database) to create and send a broadcast message within Telegram that promotes a newly posted collab. The message includes a CTA button that lets users instantly send a collab request without leaving Telegram.

⸻

User Flow (Admin)
        1.      Trigger Action
        •       Admin initiates the “New Collab Broadcast” command via the Telegram bot.
        2.      Collab Selection Menu
        •       Bot displays a list of the 5 most recent collabs (Company Name + Collab Type).
  Fetch last 5 collabs from DB (filter: active only, not expired or deleted)
        •       Admin selects one collab from the list.
        3.      Message Builder
        •       Admin is prompted to write a custom broadcast message (with basic markdown support and abilitiy to mention the user handle, so the user gets a "mention" notification on telegrram, increasing the chances of them opening the message
        •       Bot confirms the selected collab and previews the message + CTA button. Admin then has a option to send. 
        4.      Broadcast
        •       Bot sends the message to all users who have opted into notifications
        •       Message includes:
        •       Admin-written message body
        •       Primary CTA button: “Request Collab” → triggers collab request for the selected collab
  •     Secondary CTA button: View More Collabs → Takes the user to the discover page
•       Consider a /cancel command to reset state.
Confirmation Tracking
•       Show admins how many users were sent the notification
- 
⸻

User Flow (End User)
        1.      Receives Message
        •       User receives the broadcast via Telegram. The message has action buttons beneath it. 
        2.      Taps “Request Collab”
        •       A collab request is sent on behalf of the user to the collab host.
        3.      Confirmation
        •       Bot sends a confirmation message to the user: “Your collab request has been sent to [HostName]. You’ll be notified if it’s accepted.”
  - the CTA button be disabled/removed if the user has already sent a request. 
  

⸻

Requirements
        •       All interactions must be fully Telegram-native. No external app or UI loading.
        •       Admin should not need to reference a dashboard or external link.
        •       Message sending respects notification opt-in logic.
        •       Admin should be able to cancel or restart at any step.
  - Should be a fail safe for if a collab is deleted, and teh button is pressed - user given message that the collab has been deleted
•       If the user receiving the broadcast is the host of the collab being promoted, do not display the “Request Collab” button.
        •       Instead, optionally show a note as a button - 
“You’re the host of this collab – no action needed.”
The message be broadcast in just one language for now
Only allow admin accounts to initiate broadcast flow
•       Log all admin broadcasts with timestamp, collab ID, and message content for audit

⸻

## Implementation Planning

### Overview
Based on the existing codebase analysis, this feature will extend the current Telegram bot's broadcast functionality (`server/telegram.ts`) to specifically focus on collaboration promotion. The current system already supports general admin broadcasts with personalization and state management, which we'll build upon.

### Technical Architecture

#### 1. Database Schema Extensions
**No new tables required** - leveraging existing schema:
- `users.is_admin` - Admin permission validation
- `collaborations` table - Source for recent collabs list
- `requests` table - Check existing requests to disable CTA
- `notification_preferences` - Target user filtering
- Existing admin logging in `logs/admin_messages.log`

#### 2. Core Implementation Components

**A. New Telegram Bot Command: `/newcollab`**
- Location: `server/telegram.ts` 
- Add to `adminCommands` array in `setupBotCommands()` function
- Register handler: `bot.onText(/\/newcollab/, handleNewCollabBroadcast)`

**B. State Management Enhancement**
- Extend existing `adminBroadcastState` Map to support:
```typescript
type NewCollabBroadcastState = {
  state: "awaiting_collab_selection" | "awaiting_message" | "awaiting_confirmation" | "sending";
  selectedCollabId?: string;
  selectedCollabData?: CollabData;
  message?: string;
  timestamp: number;
}
```

**C. Database Query Functions**
- `getRecentActiveCollabs()` - Fetch last 5 active collaborations
- `checkExistingCollabRequest()` - Check if user already requested specific collab
- `logCollabBroadcast()` - Enhanced logging with collab ID

