### 4. Button Implementation Strategy

#### Dynamic Button Generation
```typescript
function generateCollabPromotionKeyboard(user, collab) {
  const buttons = [];
  
  if (user.id === collab.creator_id) {
    // Host gets informational button
    buttons.push([{
      text: "You're the host of this collab – no action needed",
      callback_data: `host_info_${collab.id}`
    }]);
  } else if (hasExistingRequest(user.id, collab.id)) {
    // User already requested - disabled state
    buttons.push([{
      text: "Request Already Sent ✓",
      callback_data: `already_requested_${collab.id}`
    }]);
  } else if (collabStillActive(collab)) {
    // Active collab - show request button
    buttons.push([{
      text: "Request Collab",
      callback_data: `request_collab_${collab.id}`
    }]);
  } else {
    // Collab deleted/expired - show info
    buttons.push([{
      text: "This collab is no longer available",
      callback_data: `collab_unavailable_${collab.id}`
    }]);
  }
  
  // Always include secondary CTA
  buttons.push([{
    text: "View More Collabs",
    web_app: { url: `${WEBAPP_URL}/discover` }
  }]);
  
  return { inline_keyboard: buttons };
}
```

### 5. Integration Points

#### A. Request Creation Endpoint
- Extend existing `/api/requests` endpoint to handle direct Telegram requests
- Auto-create request when "Request Collab" button pressed
- Send confirmation via `sendRequestNotification()` function

#### B. Callback Query Extensions
```typescript
// Add new handlers to existing callback_query processor:
// - "select_collab_{id}" - Collab selection
// - "request_collab_{id}" - Direct collab request
// - "host_info_{id}" - Host information
// - "already_requested_{id}" - Already requested handler
// - "collab_unavailable_{id}" - Unavailable collab handler
```

### 6. Error Handling & Edge Cases

#### A. Collab Validation
- Check collab still exists before sending requests
- Validate collab is still active/not expired
- Handle deleted collaborations gracefully

#### B. User State Management
- Timeout inactive broadcast sessions (reuse existing logic)
- Clear state on /cancel command
- Handle concurrent admin operations

#### C. Request Deduplication
- Check existing requests before allowing new ones
- Handle race conditions in request creation
- Provide clear feedback for duplicate requests

### 7. Performance Considerations

#### A. Query Optimization
- Single query for recent collabs with creator info
- Batch user preference queries (reuse existing patterns)
- Cache collab data during broadcast session

#### B. Rate Limiting
- Reuse existing broadcast rate limiting
- Add specific limits for collab request creation
- Monitor Telegram API compliance

